# Flutter Frontend Conventions

## Architecture

- State management: Riverpod (flutter_riverpod) — wrap app in ProviderScope
- Routing: go_router with GoRouter config in `routers/app_pages.dart`
- HTTP: Dio client with interceptors in `services/dio_client/`
- Storage: SharedPreferences for auth tokens, Hive for local data
- i18n: flutter_localizations + intl (en, zh)

## File Organization

```
lib/
├── models/          # Data models with fromJson/toJson
├── providers/       # Global Riverpod providers (auth, theme, locale)
├── routers/         # Route definitions and GoRouter config
├── screen/          # Feature screens, each with own providers/ and widgets/
├── services/        # API clients, Dio config, storage
├── widgets/         # Shared reusable widgets
├── utils/           # Utility functions
├── extensions/      # Dart extensions
└── mixins/          # Reusable mixins
```

## Coding Patterns

### Models

```dart
// Always handle null and type conversion in fromJson
factory Deck.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) {
  // Handle null values with defaults
  // Handle type mismatches (e.g., double → int)
}
```

### Riverpod Providers

- Screen-specific providers go in `screen/<feature>/providers/`
- Global providers go in `providers/`
- Use StateNotifier or ChangeNotifier patterns

### Screens

- Each screen is a StatelessWidget or ConsumerWidget
- Screen-specific widgets go in `screen/<feature>/widgets/`
- Use `ref.watch()` for reactive state, `ref.read()` for one-time actions

### API Calls

- All API calls go through Dio client in `services/apis/`
- Handle errors at the service layer, surface user-friendly messages

## Checks Before Commit

- `dart format .` — must pass with no changes
- `flutter analyze` — must have zero errors
- `flutter test` — all tests must pass
